name: Easy Spaghetti Squash Spaghetti
author: Tracy E
summary: This is a super easy recipe for spaghetti squash that I often eat for lunch when I am looking for something healthy and quick.
ingredients: salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
1 tablespoon freshly grated Parmesan cheese, or to taste
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Place the squash halves into a large baking dish with the cut-sides facing down
Bake in the preheated oven until easily pierced with a knife, about 40 minutes
Shred the inside of the squash with a fork and transfer to a bowl
Add olive oil, salt, and pepper to shredded squash and toss to coat
